-btn\",\"x\":278,\"y\":468,\"time\":1649656133230},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":277,\"y\":468,\"time\":1649656133233},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":280,\"y\":461,\"time\":1649656133569},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":291,\"y\":441,\"time\":1649656133586},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":304,\"y\":416,\"time\":1649656133602},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":324,\"y\":382,\"time\":1649656133619},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":346,\"y\":349,\"time\":1649656133635},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":361,\"y\":332,\"time\":1649656133652},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":368,\"y\":323,\"time\":1649656133668},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":372,\"y\":319,\"time\":1649656133686},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":373,\"y\":318,\"time\":1649656133703},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":374,\"y\":318,\"time\":1649656133719},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":374,\"y\":318,\"time\":1649656133736},{\"type\":\"click\",\"target\":\"#game-area\",\"x\":374,\"y\":318,\"time\":1649656133907},{\"type\":\"click\",\"target\":\"#game-area\",\"x\":374,\"y\":318,\"time\":1649656134231},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":374,\"y\":318,\"time\":1649656134670},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":374,\"y\":318,\"time\":1649656134704},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":374,\"y\":317,\"time\":1649656134721},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":374,\"y\":317,\"time\":1649656134737},{\"type\":\"click\",\"target\":\"#game-area\",\"x\":374,\"y\":317,\"time\":1649656134931},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":376,\"y\":308,\"time\":1649656135588},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":383,\"y\":291,\"time\":1649656135604},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":402,\"y\":250,\"time\":1649656135621},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":421,\"y\":207,\"time\":1649656135637},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":459,\"y\":137,\"time\":1649656135654},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":478,\"y\":106,\"time\":1649656135671},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":491,\"y\":84,\"time\":1649656135687},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":503,\"y\":64,\"time\":1649656135704},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":508,\"y\":57,\"time\":1649656135721},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":511,\"y\":51,\"time\":1649656135737},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":513,\"y\":48,\"time\":1649656135754},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":513,\"y\":47,\"time\":1649656135771},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":513,\"y\":45,\"time\":1649656135787},{\"type\":\"mousemove\",\"x\":513,\"y\":43,\"time\":1649656135804}],\"startTime\":1649656132136}"},{"message":"## Step 4. Augmenting Flapping Behavior\nNext, let’s replace our previous statement that added gravity with a new one. We want the bird to fall, unless it is flapping. Also, in `reset()`, let’s reset these two variables. The playing variable will come in handy later on, when we are figuring out how to implement `game over` and `reset` Try running the game again. Our bird should fly when we click! Nice!","hash":"1992d3d"},{"message":"## Step 5. Add Game Over Function\nWe will create a `gameOver()` function that manipulates the playing variable. When `playing == false`, the games stops animating movement, and the bird can't flap. Note that in this step, we only define the function, but we haven't called it yet. We will work on the game over detection in the next step.","hash":"411d701"},{"message":"## Step 6. Adding Collisions\nSadly, we have to make our bird hit things. Let’s start by adding the final piece of this, and then work backwards. In the `update()` function, let’s add an `if()` statement that checks if our bird has collided with any of the poles or hit the top or bottom of the screen. \n\n```\n// Check for collisions\nif (\n    collision(bird, poles[0]) || \n    collision(bird, poles[1]) || \n    birdTop <= 0 || \n    birdTop > containerHeight - bird.clientHeight) {\n    gameOver();\n}\n```\nThis is saying: Game Over if\n- The bird hits the top pole\n- The bird hits the bottom pole\n- The bird hits the top of the frame\n- The bird hits the bottom of the frame\n\nWe use the `collision()` function to determine whether the bird hits the poles by checking whether the bird’s boundary and the pole’s boundary are overlapping. Remember, this is a `collision()` function, so if it returns true, we’re saying, “Yes, something is colliding”. \n\nIn this session, we don’t need to implement the `collision()` function. It is provided in `collision.js`. \n\nLet’s test this out. Open up the console for this one. When you hit the bottom of the screen, fly past the top of the screen, or hit the poles, you should see the bird stop moving! Good job.","hash":"382205e"},{"message":"## Step 7. Changing Speed\nBasically, it’s working! Great job. But we can add more stuff to make the game more fully-featured. The two big things we can add are: a Score counter, and a changing speed.\n\nLet's first change the speed as the bird passes more poles.\nIn `updatePoles()`, we checked whether the poles went outside of the game area. Thus, we can update the speed here as new poles generated. We do this by adding `speed += 0.25`.\n\nWe’re manipulating the speed variable, but where does it actually affect the scene? Look in `updatePoles()`, where it says `pole.style.right = ${polesCurrentPos + speed}px`; Because this function runs every frame, the speed variable determines how far the poles move every frame. As speed increases, the faster the poles move across the screen.\n\nLet’s test it out!\n\nYou should see “2” for speed. However, once 4 poles pass by you, you should see the speed increase to 3, and you should feel the game getting faster. That is because the game speed increases by 0.25 every time they pass!","hash":"ead419d"},{"message":"## Step 8. Changing Score\nFinally, let’s add a working scoreboard! This has a lot of similar changes to the previous step: We'll be adding to the HTML, adding some new variables in the JS, and then augmenting them as the game progresses. \n\nWhen a pole goes outside of the game area, we update the score value, as well as the display of the score. We also want to update the `reset` function so that the score is reset to 0 when restarting the game.","hash":"e3b5233"},{"message":"## Complete\nGreat job! Our flappy bird game is fully functioning. I hope you learned something and had fun : )","hash":""}]
